Yahaya Bello has been reelected as the governor of Kogi State. The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC), on Monday, declared the All Progressives Congress (APC) governorship candidate, as the winner of the governorship election held in the state on Saturday, November, Punch reports. Governor Bello polled a total of 406,222 votes to defeat his major opponent, Musa Wada of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), who polled 189,704 votes to emerge second. The returning governor and his wife celebrated the election at the Kogi State Government House.      Photo Credit: @channelstv The post Yahaya Bello is Declared Winner of Kogi State Gubernatorial Election appeared first on BellaNaija â€“ Showcasing Africa to the world. Read today!. Source: Bella Naija